Titolo: Zany Golf

Anno: 1988

Descrizione: Zany Golf, also known as Will Harvey's Zany Golf, is a fantasy take on miniature golf developed by Sandcastle Productions and published by Electronic Arts 1988. The game was originally written for the Apple IIGS and subsequently ported to the Amiga, Atari ST, and MS-DOS machines. In 1990 a port was released for the Sega Genesis. The game was developed by Will Harvey, Ian Gooding, Jim Nitchals, and Douglas Fulton. Harvey was pursuing his advanced degrees at Stanford University at the time.The game is played in a 3D isometric viewpoint and allows up to 4 players. Zany Golf consists of half a golf course—nine holes—plus a bonus hole.